r frequencies. We suggest that an extra\nopacity, sensitively dependent on frequency, is likely to account for the\ndifference at lower frequencies. The evolution of the magnetic field\n(determined from synchrotron self absorption turn-over) is roughly consistent\nwith $B \\propto t^{-1}$. Radio spectral index in the optically thin part\nevolves from $\\alpha \\sim 0.8-1.0$ at few tens of days to $\\sim 0.6$ in about\n10 years.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 May 2004 13:43:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
