tes inside and a DM\ncomponent that dominates outwards. An appendix gives the virial mass dependence\nof the concentration parameter, central density, and total mass of the Navarro\net al. model. In a 2nd appendix are given single integral expressions for the\nvelocity dispersions averaged along the line-of-sight, in circular apertures\nand in thin slits, for general luminosity density and mass distributions, with\nisotropic orbits.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 May 2004 15:23:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 16 May 2005 15:39:24 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 24 May 2005 09:01:19 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 11 Dec 2014 22:49:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-12-15"}
